> There&#x27;s no (easy) way to send US traffic to the Amazon.com site<p>You can run a small snippet of JS that replaces all the links with amazon.co.uk to amazon.com. You have to figure out that the user is from the US (maybe reading the Accept-Language, don&#x27;t know if that&#x27;s reliable)<p><pre><code>    // untested
    var links = document.getElementsByTagName(&#x27;a&#x27;);
    for (i=0; i<links.length; i++){
        var link = links[i];
        if (link.href.match(/amazon.co.uk/))
            link.href = link.href.replace(&#x27;.co.uk&#x27;, &#x27;.com&#x27;)
    }</code></pre>

